Here is a simple function in Python to combine a list of strings:

```python
def concat_strings(lst):
    return ''.join(lst)
```

This function uses the `''.join()` method which takes an iterable (in this case, a list) and returns a single string with all elements joined using the given separator ('', by default). In our example, we simply pass the input list as it is.

